{"article_id":"l7PGYmsvzVkLIc82","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Washington ( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The Senate intelligence committee will grill Attorney General Jeff Sessions Tuesday afternoon ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"just as a slew of new questions about him have bubbled to the top of the Russia probes .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Former FBI Director James Comey launched Sessions into the spotlight with his own testimony last week .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Now Sessions will take the same stage .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Lawmakers have already aired many of their concerns about their former colleague","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"-- from his meetings with the Russian ambassador to the US to his role in the firing of Comey .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"And then an ally of President Donald Trump suggested","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"the President is thinking about firing the special counsel","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"investigating the Russia issue .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"1 . How many times did Sessions meet with Sergey Kislyak ?","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Sessions recused himself from overseeing the federal probe into ties between the Trump campaign and Russian officials ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"just a day after The Washington Post reported","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that he had two undisclosed meetings with Sergey Kislyak , the Russian ambassador to the US .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"But reports of a possible third meeting between Sessions and Kislyak have occupied congressional investigators since then .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Comey ,","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"according to sources ,","depth":13},{"id":17,"text":"told senators","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"that investigators overheard Russians discussing a third , private meeting","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"Sessions had with Kislyak .","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"( Sessions ' spokespeople have denied","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"a third meeting happened . )","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"Two Democrats on the Senate Judiciary Committee","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"-- Sens . Al Franken and Patrick Leahy","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"-- who initially pressed Sessions in his confirmation hearings on Russian contacts --","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"wrote to Comey","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"seeking an investigation","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"into whether Sessions perjured himself","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"when he said","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"he had no contacts .","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"2 . Why did Comey assume","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Sessions would recuse himself earlier","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"than he did ?","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"While answering questions","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"about why he did n't alert other officials about Trump 's request","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"that he end his investigation of former national security adviser Michael Flynn ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"Comey said","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"that FBI officials long expected Sessions to recuse himself from overseeing the Russia probe .","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"JUST WATCHED Sessions , from Eagle Scout to attorney general","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"MUST WATCH Sessions , from Eagle Scout to attorney general 02:18","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"`` Our judgment ,","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"as I recall ,","depth":14},{"id":43,"text":"was that he was very close to and inevitably going to recuse himself for a variety of reasons .","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"We also were aware of facts","depth":14},{"id":45,"text":"that I ca n't discuss in an open setting","depth":15},{"id":46,"text":"that would make his continued engagement in a Russia-related investigation problematic , ''","depth":15},{"id":47,"text":"Comey said .","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"The `` variety of reasons '' line ,","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"followed by admonishment","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"that he could n't discuss the answer in an open setting","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"perked a lot of ears .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"Why would Comey think","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"Sessions was going to recuse himself ?","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"The view of the US attorney general","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"coming before a group of aggressive senators","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"may paint a picture similar to the media bonanza of Comey 's blockbuster hearing last week .","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"But it 's more likely to resemble the public hearing","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"that happened just a day before Comey ,","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"where four top intelligence officials were grilled mercilessly ,","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"but offered little information .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"At one point , Director of National Intelligence Dan Coats cautioned","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"that he would have to consult with the White House counsel 's office","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"before even answering questions in a classified session","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"because they may invoke executive privilege .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"It 's all led to a critical question","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"of when and if Sessions will cite privilege","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"-- used by presidents","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"to block testimony before Congress by their aides on certain topics .","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"Even the standard process itself","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"of invoking executive privilege","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"could be jumbled by the Russia probe .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"Invoking of executive privilege for administration employees is typically formally announced by the attorney general ,","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"but it 's not exactly clear","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"who would make the formal announcement for Sessions ,","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"said Michael Bahar , former Democratic staff director for the House intelligence committee and former White House lawyer .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"`` Everything is being looked at anew , as of late , ''","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"said Bahar ,","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"who now runs the cybersecurity practice for Eversheds Sutherland US in Washington .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"The tool covers discussions with the president ,","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"Bahar noted ,","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"and could be used","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"to protect discussions of Comey 's firing and questions about the President 's request to Comey","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"to drop the Flynn investigation .","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"Sessions and Trump have been close allies for more than a year now","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"-- Sessions was Trump 's earliest supporter in the Senate","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"and his top staff became some of Trump 's most important advisers .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"Also , the two were together on issues like immigration and trade","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"when , at the time , Sessions was often a voice in the wilderness among other Senate Republicans .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"Paul :","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"Look at facts ,","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"but Russia investigation all 'sour grapes '","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"Paul :","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"Look at facts ,","depth":15},{"id":97,"text":"but Russia investigation all 'sour grapes '","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"01:59","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"That 's why the reports last week","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"that Sessions offered to resign over a new , incredible strain between the two ,","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"was pretty surprising .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"Multiple reports have cited sources","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"that central to that split was Trump 's belief","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"that Sessions should never have recused himself from overseeing the Russia probe .","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"( And , implicitly , that Sessions would be in a position","depth":15},{"id":107,"text":"to `` lift the cloud '' of the Russia investigation","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"if he was still overseeing it . )","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"Sessions certainly is n't expected to hit his boss","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"while testifying on live television ,","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"but look for senators to try and get at how much pressure Trump has put on him .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"5 . Why was Sessions involved in the firing of Comey","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"if he had stepped aside from the Russia probe ?","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"Sessions stepped aside from the Russia probe on March 2 .","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"But , two months later , he was involved in the firing of the FBI official","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"overseeing that probe .","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"Senate Democrats have been champing at the bit for more than a month now","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"to get an answer to what exactly Sessions meant","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"when he said","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"he was recusing himself .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"Sen. Ron Wyden , a member of the intelligence committee , told reporters","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"he plans to press Sessions on his recusal .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"`` Based on everything","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"I know ,","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"this is n't close to what people believe is a real recusal !","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"When you 're recusing yourself ,","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"you are stepping aside","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"and this sure does n't look like it , ''","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"Wyden said ,","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"referring to Sessions ' involvement in the firing letters to Comey .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"it compromises sources or methods","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"or in any way harms America 's position in the world ,","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"so we 'll start with that , ''","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"Wyden said .","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"`` But there are a host of issues","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"that relate to his recusal , what he may of known about Mike Flynn , that sort of thing . ''","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"Newsmax CEO and Trump friend Chris Ruddy rung the alarms Monday ,","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"that Trump was seriously considering firing Robert Mueller ,","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"who is leading the federal Russia probe .","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"since the President can not directly fire the special counsel ,","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"the question lands squarely at the feet of Sessions and Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein .","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"This prompts the question ,","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"would Sessions support the President","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"and fire the special counsel ,","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"if he requested it ?","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"But ,","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"because Sessions has recused himself ,","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"the question could easily fall to Rosenstein .","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"Both officials are testifying on the Hill Tuesday .","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"And would Sessions and Rosenstein risk being fired themselves","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"and refuse to fire Mueller ?","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"CORRECTION :","depth":3},{"id":156,"text":"This story has been updated","depth":4},{"id":157,"text":"to correct Michael Bahar 's law firm .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":315,"left":0,"right":314,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":314,"left":311,"right":313,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":311,"left":166,"right":310,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":161,"right":165,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":159,"right":160,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":165,"left":162,"right":164,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":162,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":7,"right":163,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":163,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":310,"left":267,"right":309,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":267,"left":185,"right":266,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":185,"left":10,"right":184,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":184,"left":176,"right":183,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":168,"right":175,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":168,"left":11,"right":167,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":175,"left":14,"right":174,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":172,"right":173,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":170,"right":171,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":170,"left":169,"right":17,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":169,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":20,"right":21,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":183,"left":179,